# Tailwind + CVA

## Tokens first

Atlas exposes a design token layer in `src/tokens.ts` and maps them to Tailwind
theme extensions in `tailwind.config.ts`. Always reach for a token:

- Colors: `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-input`
- Spacing: the 4px scale (`gap-2`, `px-4`) — do not use arbitrary values like `gap-[7px]`
- Radii: `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg` — do not use `rounded-[9px]`
- Typography: `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg` — font sizes are capped by tokens

Arbitrary values are a code smell. If you need a value not in the token set,
the token set probably needs expanding — open a design-token PR first.

## Class ordering

Prettier's `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` handles sorting. Do not reorder
manually.

## `cn()` helper

Every class string passes through `cn()` in `src/lib/cn.ts` — it merges
duplicate utilities (e.g., a base `p-4` overridden by consumer's `p-2`):

```tsx
import { cn } from '~/lib/cn';

<div className={cn('p-4 bg-card', className)} />
```

Never use string concatenation or template literals to build classnames.

## Variants with `cva`

For components with multiple states, use `cva` — never handwrite variant maps.

```ts
import { cva } from 'class-variance-authority';

export const badgeVariants = cva(
  'inline-flex items-center rounded-full text-xs font-medium',
  {
    variants: {
      tone: {
        neutral: 'bg-muted text-muted-foreground',
        success: 'bg-success/10 text-success',
        warning: 'bg-warning/10 text-warning',
        danger: 'bg-danger/10 text-danger'
      },
      size: {
        sm: 'px-2 py-0.5',
        md: 'px-2.5 py-1'
      }
    },
    defaultVariants: { tone: 'neutral', size: 'md' }
  }
);
```

Variant values are always declared on the variant map, never inferred from
string unions.

## Dark mode

Atlas uses class-based dark mode (`dark:`). Every component must look correct
in both themes. For tokens that differ between themes, define the token at the
CSS variable level — do not scatter `dark:` variants across components.

## Don't

- Don't write custom CSS files for components — utilities only
- Don't use `!important` — override specificity with token changes or `cn()` merging
- Don't animate with CSS keyframes in component files — use Tailwind's `animate-*` utilities or Framer Motion
- Don't use `style={{…}}` except for dynamic positioning (tooltip/popover transforms)
- Don't use `@apply` in a component — if you want reusability, make it a variant
